The Supreme Court of Appeal in Bloemfontein. JOHANNESBURG – Five new judges have been appointed to the Supreme Court of Appeal. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced the appointments following recommendations made by the Judicial Service Commission as prescribed by the Constitution of the country. The group of new appointments includes three women. READ: Ramaphosa shows that he's in control. But does he have what it takes to win? The following judges have been appointed; Justice Daniel Vuminkosi Dlodlo Justice Caroline Elizabeth Heaton Nicholls Justice Fikile Eunice Mokgohloa Justice Yvonne Thokozile Mbatha Justice Clive Michael Plasket Justice Xola Mlungisi Petse has also been appointed as Deputy Judge President of the Supreme Court of Appeal. The President has wished the justices well in their new positions. “These appointments - of which three are women, reflect government’s commitment to the ongoing transformation of the Bench,” Ramaphosa said.